        <div class=3D"row">
            <div class=3D"col">
                <h1 class=3D"grandnational sra-page-heading sra-gold mt-3 m=
b-3">Reference Lap Times</h1>

                <p><strong>Reference lap times</strong> provide a way for u=
s to compare your pace with other drivers in the league for better division=
 placement during season championship events. This helps to ensure that dri=
vers with similar pace are grouped together before each race for a better o=
nline racing experience for everyone.</p>

                <p>For each track below, a multiplier is applied to each re=
ference lap time to determine a drivers division. A reference lap time is a=
 competitive lap time for a particular track.</p>

                <p>Check out the hot lap and hot stint tables below of trac=
k lap times and note your division based on your overall pace over several =
clean, consecutive laps. Your average clean lap time should be <strong>fast=
er</strong> than the division lap times below to be eligible to be assigned=
 to that division. If you are just starting out with sim racing, you can re=
quest to be placed in the lowest division.<!-- We also host live track coac=
hing sessions on <a class=3D"sra-gold-hover text-decoration-underline" href=
=3D"https://discord.gg/SimRacingAlliance">Discord</a> with practice events =
hosted by professional sim racers on <a class=3D"sra-gold-hover text-decora=
tion-underline" href=3D"/calendar">Thursday nights</a> if you would like to=
 participate and help to improve your sim racing skills!--></p>

                <p>Once you have set some clean laps, take a look at our <a=
 class=3D"sra-gold-hover text-decoration-underline" href=3D"https://www.sim=
racingalliance.com/leaderboards">leaderboards</a> and compare your lap time=
s to other drivers on your preferred track to see how you rank compared to =
the rest of the league. If you would like to join a Sim Racing Alliance pra=
ctice server before being assigned a division, <a class=3D"sra-gold-hover t=
ext-decoration-underline" href=3D"https://discord.gg/SimRacingAlliance">joi=
n our Discord</a> and follow the channel instructions for <a class=3D"sra-g=
old-hover text-decoration-underline" href=3D"https://discord.com/channels/9=
15686674833498203/925126126555254825" target=3D"_blank">ACC server informat=
ion</a>.</p>

                <p class=3D"small text-gray-600">Note: Reference lap times =
are calculated from <a class=3D"sra-gold-hover text-decoration-underline" h=
ref=3D"https://gosetups.gg/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/GO_Setups_Lap_Times.p=
df?ref=3D5879" target=3D"_blank">GO Setups</a> leaderboards over a select n=
umber of GT3 cars. Lap times assume optimal dry track conditions with an ap=
proximate 21=C2=B0C ambient air temperature.</p>

